snippet.title: ☆ 3 WAYS TO MULTIPLY BINOMIALS
snippet.description:
Join us on this flipped math lesson where we visually explore how to multiply binomials using FOIL, the Distributive Method, and the Box Method. For more MashUp Math content, visit http://www.mashupmath.com and join our free mailing list! :)

Get the PDF Lesson Guide here: http://mashupmath.com/resources/

This lesson answers the questions: How do I multiply binomials? What is the product of two binomials? What is FOIL? How do I multiply binomials using the box method? What is DOTS? What are factors? What is the distributive method?

Our lessons are perfect for flipped classroom math teachers and students. This lesson is aligned with the common core learning standards for math and the SAT math curriculum as well.

Be sure to join our mailing list at http://www.mashupmath.com
